@node "What's new" "What's new"
@next "Requirements"
@prev "Main"

                       @{b}@{bg shine}What's new? - V1.1@{ub}@{bg back}

Not much new really, but what there is should be damn handy for some
people

      - The keyboard controls can now be re-defined. To do this, run the
        program called "DefineKeys" before running the game. Unfortunately
        you can't redefine them during the game yet, because that would
        involve re-writing the front-end code which I really don't have
        time for at present :( Please note that if you change the keys
        then the select players screen will have the wrong keys
        displayed at the bottom.

      - You can now see who is on your team when looking at the scores in
        a team game (wow, what a big improvement! :-)

Other new stuff that you would have if you registered (see @{"Support" link "Support" 0}) :-

      - The "Wobble Mode". Blob not mad enough for you? Try playing with the
        screen wobbling about all over the place every now and again. Even
        more manic than usual!

      - New level format thing. You can now easily set the order in which you
        want to play the levels. (Thats's all 14 of our levels, plus the
        thousands you can design yourself using the Blob Level-Grabber!)


@endnode

