                           @{b}@{bg shine}The Menus@{ub}@{bg back}

    The main menu:-

      @{"Normal game" link "The Game" 0} - start the game, everyone against everyone else.
      @{"Team game" link "Team Games" 0} - start a team game.
      Options - go to the options menu.
      Quit - Hmmmm, wonder what this does?

    Options menu:-

      Random levels/Start at Level #

           -If random levels is selected, the levels will be played in a
            random order. If not, the levels will be played sequentially,
            starting at level #.

      Full sound/No boing

           -When there are lots of players, the boing sound effect can
            really start to annoy, so this enables you to turn it off.
            (This can also be achieved from within the game by pressing
            F1, whilst F2 turns it back on)

      Main Menu - surprise, surprise, back to the main menu!

@endnode

@node "The Game" "The Game"
@next "Team Games"
@prev "The Menus"

                            @{b}@{bg shine}The Game@{ub}@{bg back}

    Once you have selected your choice of game, you then get to choose
  how many rounds to have in the league. This number is limited to the
  number of different levels available (Twelve at the last count, unless
  you've added some of your own)

    You then go to the select players screen. Each set of controls is listed
  along the middle of the screen. Press fire when the arrow is above a set
  of controls to turn the corresponding player on or off. A Blob shows that
  the player is active, no Blob means inactive. Select done when you are
  finished. If you are playing a @{"Team game" link "Team Games" 0}, then this screen will be slightly
  different.

    Once you are done, the fun begins. All players start by dropping from
  the top of the screen. Jump by pressing fire (The height of the jump is
  determined by how long you hold down the button). Basically, try to land
  on the other players, and avoid being landed on yourself. If you die, you
  re-appear from a random point at the top of the screen.

    Bonuses are available for many things, such as dive-bombing, multiple
  kills and other amazing feats. Anti-bonuses are also awarded, for those
  of you who are truly useless.

    When there are only 15 seconds left in the round, an alarm will sound.
  If at this point you have lots more points than everyone else, you may
  get a price on your head. If so, anyone who kills you gets bonus points.
  (Double or triple points depending on how far ahead you are)

  Beware of performing very badly if you have a price on your head, it
  can be highly detrimental to your league score.

    At the end of a round, the scores are calculated as follows:-

    -Two league points are awarded for every kill notched up.
    -Players are ranked acording to no. of kills, then points awarded as
     follows:-
              1st  28 pts       (When draws occur, the points for both
              2nd  24 pts        positions are divided equally between
              3rd  20 pts        the players)
              4th  16 pts
              5th  12 pts
              6th  8 pts
              7th  4 pts
              8th  0 pts

    -Bonuses - Well, the better it is, the more points it scores.
               (And vice versa of course)

@endnode

@node "Team Games"
@next "Support"
@prev "The Game"

                          @{b}@{bg shine}Team Games@{ub}@{bg back}

    Team games enable you to have more than one player contributing
  to one league score. The game proceeds as normal, except that no points
  are scored  for killing your own team members. League scores are then
  combined for the members of each team. You can have as many teams as you
  like, so if some people are really bad, you can even the odds by making
  them a team.

    The select players screen is different for team games. Above the list
  of controllers there is a number. This is the number of the team this
  player belongs to. Cycle through the teams by pressing fire with the
  pointer above the number in question. If no number is shown then the
  player is inactive.

@endnode

